Viewing the docs
------------------

Install lpEdit

>>> cd docs
>>> python initDocs.py

Using github pages
------------------

(1) clone a new repo to start fresh
    
    ~$ git clone git@github.com:ajrichards/hts-integrate.git htsint-docs

(2) create a new branch

    ~$ cd htsint-docs
    ~$ git checkout --orphan gh-pages
    ~$ git pull origin gh-pages

(3) remove all files from the working directory

    ~$ git rm -rf .

(4) copy the website into the repo for example

    ~$ cp -r ~/projects/hts-integrate/docs/_sphinx/_build/* .

(5) github does not like folders with leading underscores so

    ~$ touch .nojekyll

(5) commit and push to github

    ~$ git add * .nojekyll
    ~$ git commit -m 'first docs commit'
    ~$ git push origin gh-pages


